
Open Source Components in SCO OpenServer and SCO UnixWare
Description: This session will outline SCO's ongoing plans and commitment to
open source components as part of the platform product, underscoring SCO's
value add in testing, integrating, maintaining and supporting the components 
that are supplied. The bulk of the session will be a technical overview of the 
open source technologies in SCO OpenServer and SCO UnixWare today, explaining
what the technologies are and how they may be deployed. Examples include:
         o Apache Web Server
         o Samba File and Print Server
         o PostgreSQL and MySQL data bases
         o Squid Proxy Server
         o GNU Development Tools
